[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    149[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ### Logical flow
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    150[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The pipeline follows a clear pedagogical progression:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    151[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 1. Config (what levers exist) -> 2. Data (what inputs look like) -> 3. Training (how the model learns) -> 4. Evaluation (how we know it works) -> 5. Scoring (how we use it) -> 6. Storage (where results go) -> 7. S3 upload (SageMaker handoff)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    152[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    153[0m:[38;5;10m[49m This ordering builds understanding incrementally. Each step's comments reference why it exists in the broader clinical workflow.
